<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="MuTA21">
<l>pēcuvā revvaḷavu pēcuva ravvaḷavē</l>
<l>vāca malarttuḻāy mālaiyāṉ – ṟēcuṭaiya</l>
<l>cakkarattāṉ caṅkiṉāṉ cārṅkattāṉ poṅkarava</l>
<l>vakkaraṉaik koṉṟāṉ vaṭivu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>To the extent that they talk, they will talk<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For the emulation of the Sanskrit relative construction in Tamil, see also Po. 44 and note.</note></l>
<l>about the form of him who killed Vakkaraṉ<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">Vakkaraṉ is identified by the vyākyānam with Skt. Dantavakra, but stories vary, and here the only detail given is that Viṣṇu killed him.</note> with a rising howl,</l>
<l>the one with a garland of tulsi in fragrant blossoms, the one with the</l> 
<l>fiery discus, the one with the conch, the one with the [bow], Śārṅga.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
